      "Discovered models originate from models.json and may contain persistence markers.",
      "Build a more helpful error when the model is not found. Local providers (ollama, vllm) need a dummy API key to be registered. Users often configure `agents.defaults.model.primary: \"ollama/\u2026\"` but forget to set `OLLAMA_API_KEY`, resulting in a confusing \"Unknown model\" error.  This detects known providers that require opt-in auth and adds a hint. See: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/17328"
